# Testing Conventions

## Structure

Tests mirror `src/` layout:

```
tests/
  unit/
    modules/
      search/
        application/    ← test use cases with mocked repo
        domain/         ← test domain logic in isolation
      agents/
        application/
  integration/
    modules/
      search/           ← test against real OpenSearch (docker-compose)
  e2e/                  ← full HTTP request/response via TestClient
  conftest.py           ← shared fixtures (app, http client)
```

## Unit Tests — Rules

- Mock **all** I/O: OpenSearch, LLM clients, HTTP, filesystem
- Test **one behaviour** per test — no multi-assert mega-tests
- No `@pytest.mark.asyncio` needed — `asyncio_mode = "auto"` is set globally

```python
# ✅ CORRECT — pure logic test with mocked repo
async def test_execute_search_returns_empty_on_no_hits(mock_search_repo):
    mock_search_repo.search.return_value = []
    use_case = ExecuteSearchUseCase(repo=mock_search_repo)
    result = await use_case.execute(SearchQuery(text="unknown"))
    assert result.hits == []
```

## Integration Tests — Rules

- Use **real OpenSearch** started via docker-compose
- Do **not** mock LLM clients in integration tests — use a stub/fake implementation
- Each test must clean up its index data (`yield` fixture with teardown)

## Fixtures

- Fixtures go in `conftest.py` at the **nearest appropriate level**
- Do not leak fixtures across levels (unit fixtures must not be used in integration)
- Name fixtures clearly: `mock_search_repo`, `opensearch_client`, `test_app`

## Naming

Pattern: `test_<what>_<condition>_<expected_outcome>`

```python
# ✅
async def test_execute_search_with_empty_query_raises_validation_error(): ...
async def test_opensearch_repo_returns_hits_sorted_by_score(): ...

# ❌
async def test_search(): ...
async def test_1(): ...
```
